{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52db7c7e-fd05-48c7-94e5-fd4f4a67c506","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates crash reports — no `createdump` needed:\n\n1. **Check the system crash report directory:**\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   Look for `.ips` files matching your process name (e.g., `YourApp_2026-05-10-*.ips`).\n\n2. **Also check the system-wide location:**\n   ```\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n\n3. **Use Console.app** → sidebar → *Crash Reports* for a GUI view.\n\n4. **For core dumps** (if enabled):\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited   # enable before running\n   ```\n   Core files land in `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\nThe `.ips` crash log contains the native backtrace with addresses. If you need to symbolicate the .NET runtime frames in that `.ips` file, I can help with that too — just share the file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f7fd433e-c92c-45f4-a529-0809c964fb21","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app that crashed on macOS, and they don't have `createdump` available. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to search any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":316,"requestId":"6082:1230E4:2D2F29:3AFA24:69FFE421"},"id":"f7976441-2af9-4b0b-b243-ea0efcadb083","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:49:30.011Z","parentId":"a12038e5-8bf8-478c-9142-0616f45fdd55"}
